OL,3,CTeam Reform smashes Plymouth's
OL,4,Cpolitical duopoly on dramatic election
OL,5,Cnight
OL,7,FSince the mid 1970s, the city council
OL,8,Fhere has been run by either Labour or
OL,9,Fthe Conservatives. We have seen brief
OL,10,Fspells of 'no overall control', when
OL,11,Fthe parties have been unable to
OL,12,Fcommand an overall majority, but
OL,13,Fsmaller groups have always remained on
OL,14,Fthe sidelines, scrapping for survival,
OL,15,Funable to break into the top tier.
OL,16,FUntil now.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,437,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F436A1778415071
OL,3,CTeam Reform smashes Plymouth's
OL,4,Cpolitical duopoly on dramatic election
OL,5,Cnight
OL,7,FThe football analogy is rather
OL,8,Ffitting. When two big clubs dominate
OL,9,Ffor a long stretch of time, it can
OL,10,Ffeel like a stranglehold which may
OL,11,Fnever be broken.
OL,13,FThe spectacle of fierce rivals taking
OL,14,Flumps out of each other, building an
OL,15,Fintense feud over generations, brings
OL,16,Fits own particular brand of sporting
OL,17,Fdrama. But when an outsider arrives to
OL,18,Fthreaten the duopoly, all bets are off.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,437,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F436A1778415071
OL,3,CTeam Reform smashes Plymouth's
OL,4,Cpolitical duopoly on dramatic election
OL,5,Cnight
OL,7,FIt is important to stress that Labour,
OL,8,Fand their veteran leader Tudor Evans,
OL,9,Fstill run the council, with 31 seats
OL,10,Fto Reform's 16. But this was a seismic
OL,11,Fresult, which saw several 'big beasts'
OL,12,Fof the council chamber lose their
OL,13,Fseats.
OL,15,FVeteran Labour councillors like Bill
OL,16,FStevens, Tina Tuohy and former MP
OL,17,FAlison Raynsford, all of whom have
OL,18,Fdecades of experience serving their
OL,19,Fconstituents, were all beaten by
OL,20,FReform.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,437,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F436A1778415071
OL,3,CTeam Reform smashes Plymouth's
OL,4,Cpolitical duopoly on dramatic election
OL,5,Cnight
OL,7,FThey all represented the more deprived
OL,8,Fsouthern areas of Plymouth, close to
OL,9,Fthe dockyard and the naval base,
OL,10,Fhistorically Labour strongholds.
OL,11,FHistory, it seems, is no longer a
OL,12,Freliable barometer of the future.
OL,14,FCouncillor Steve Ricketts, who himself
OL,15,Fstarted out as a Conservative member
OL,16,Fbefore going independent, now faces
OL,17,Fthe prospect of leading the second
OL,18,Flargest party into the council chamber
OL,19,Fas the city's official opposition.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
